cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image denoising, image inpainting, and image annotation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a discriminative sparse coding algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions the use of label information for image annotation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, cs.AI. The paper also deals with multiview features, which can be categorized under multimedia, cs.MM. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on the PASCAL VOC'07 dataset, which is a benchmark dataset for information retrieval, cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
